---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="TexTools Guide" description="How to run TexTools on Linux with Wine/Proton for FF14 mods">
  <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 1.5rem;">
    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
    <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 0.85rem; color: #8a8fa8;">
      <a href="/" style="color: #8a8fa8; text-decoration: none;" onmouseover="this.style.color='#c8a96e'" onmouseout="this.style.color='#8a8fa8'">Home</a>
      <span>›</span>
      <a href="/guides" style="color: #8a8fa8; text-decoration: none;" onmouseover="this.style.color='#c8a96e'" onmouseout="this.style.color='#8a8fa8'">Guides</a>
      <span>›</span>
      <span style="color: #c8a96e;">TexTools</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Header -->
    <div style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 9999px; background-color: rgba(200,169,110,0.15); color: #c8a96e; font-weight: 600;">Medium</span>
      </div>
      <h1 style="font-size: 2.25rem; font-weight: 800; color: #e8e0d0; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">TexTools on Linux</h1>
      <p style="color: #8a8fa8; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7;">
        TexTools is a Windows application for directly modifying FF14 files.
        On Linux it can be run through Wine or inside the Proton prefix.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="background-color: rgba(200,80,80,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(200,80,80,0.3); border-radius: 10px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
      <p style="color: #e05a5a; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Important</p>
      <p style="color: #8a8fa8; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
        TexTools modifies FF14 files directly. Always create a <strong style="color: #e8e0d0;">backup</strong>
        before installing any mods. Use the built-in backup feature in TexTools.
        For most use cases, <a href="/guides/penumbra" style="color: #c8a96e;">Penumbra</a> is the better choice.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Step 1: Download TexTools</h2>
      <p>
        Download TexTools from the official source.
        You need the Windows version (<code>.exe</code> or <code>.zip</code>).
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Official website: <strong>textools.net</strong></li>
        <li>Download the latest version as a ZIP archive</li>
        <li>Extract it to a location of your choice, e.g. <code>~/tools/textools</code></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Step 2: Prepare the Wine prefix</h2>
      <p>
        TexTools requires .NET Framework. Set up a separate Wine prefix:
      </p>
      <pre><code>WINEPREFIX=~/.wine-textools WINEARCH=win64 winecfg</code></pre>
      <p>
        Then install .NET Framework 4.8 with Winetricks:
      </p>
      <pre><code>WINEPREFIX=~/.wine-textools winetricks dotnet48</code></pre>

      <div class="callout callout-info">
        <strong style="color: #4a90d9;">Tip:</strong> If Winetricks is not installed:
        <code>sudo pacman -S winetricks</code> (Arch) or <code>sudo apt install winetricks</code> (Debian/Ubuntu)
      </div>

      <h2>Step 3: Launch TexTools</h2>
      <pre><code>WINEPREFIX=~/.wine-textools wine ~/tools/textools/FFXIV_TexTools.exe</code></pre>

      <p>
        On first launch, TexTools will ask for the FF14 installation path.
        Provide the path within the Wine filesystem.
        Your Linux home directory is accessible under <code>Z:\</code>:
      </p>
      <pre><code># Example for Steam:
Z:\home\YOURNAME\.steam\steam\steamapps\common\FINAL FANTASY XIV Online</code></pre>

      <h2>Step 4: Create a backup</h2>
      <p>
        Before installing any mod, back up the original files:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Go to <strong>Help → Backup Index Files</strong></li>
        <li>Choose a safe location for the backup</li>
        <li>Wait for the process to complete</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Step 5: Install a mod</h2>
      <p>
        TexTools supports <code>.ttmp</code> and <code>.ttmp2</code> files:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Go to <strong>Mods → Import ModPack</strong></li>
        <li>Select the <code>.ttmp2</code> file</li>
        <li>Review the list of files that will be changed</li>
        <li>Click <strong>Import</strong></li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Reverting mods</h2>
      <p>
        If something goes wrong or you want to remove all mods:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Go to <strong>Mods → Revert All Mods</strong></li>
        <li>Alternatively: <strong>Help → Restore Index Files</strong> (uses your backup)</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Using Proton instead of a separate Wine</h2>
      <p>
        Alternatively, you can run TexTools inside the FF14 Proton prefix.
        Find the Proton prefix for your FF14 installation:
      </p>
      <pre><code># Steam App ID for FF14: 39210
~/.steam/steam/steamapps/compatdata/39210/pfx/</code></pre>
      <pre><code>WINEPREFIX=~/.steam/steam/steamapps/compatdata/39210/pfx \
  wine ~/tools/textools/FFXIV_TexTools.exe</code></pre>
      <p>
        The advantage: TexTools can then access FF14 files directly through the Windows path.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid #2a2f3e;">
      <a href="/guides" style="color: #8a8fa8; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.9rem;" onmouseover="this.style.color='#c8a96e'" onmouseout="this.style.color='#8a8fa8'">← All Guides</a>
      <a href="/guides/penumbra" style="color: #c8a96e; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.9rem;">Penumbra →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
